      "span_text": "The plug can be removed by phospholipase and was therefore ascribed to phospholipid.  In our model, hydrophobic residues line the central cavity on the periplasmic side, whereas it is lined by bulky, polar side-chains (Tyr34, Lys38 and Glu41) on the cytoplasmic side."
